Located in Spain in the Costa Brava area, the village of Estartit is a privileged place to spend a vacation. Rich in diverse landscapes, a huge beach and a range of sports and fun, this village will please the whole family. Strolling through its old streets or along Santa Anna Street will allow you to feel the life of yesteryear as well as maritime traditions.

This station also hides nooks and crannies with incredible and wild landscapes, towards the coasts. Boat excursions along the cliffs allow you to admire its exceptional natural architecture.

L'Estartit has a wide variety of water activities, from surfing to scuba diving, stand-up paddle boarding and windsurfing.
